PixeLens is a modelling program for strong gravitational lenses.

It is free software under the GNU GPL. See COPYING for license details.

Developed by Prasenjit Saha (mostly 2001-2007)
and Jonathan Coles (2005-2007)


To build from source
====================

1. Make sure the javatangle preprocessor (part of Rambutan) is installed.

2. Set the PUB directory in makefile.common

3. Run the following make command

   make -sf makefile.PixeLens

